name: Print Media II
description: This course is a continuation of FAS232H with an introduction to screenprinting. The integration of hand drawn and digital imagery is emphasized, while students may incorporate bookworks, drawing, installation, and other media. Focus is placed upon individual development through research and production; students are encouraged to link their ideas with the spectrum of media and skills that are most suited to their individual goals.[72P] Prerequisite or Corequisite: FAS232H5/P.I.
